Now that you’ve defined your `session.id`, let’s make sure it works.  

In Honeycomb, open the Query Builder and add the specific `session.id` to the WHERE clause. This will show you a specific user session. Then, filter by `is_root` to view only root spans. GROUP BY `trace.trace_id` and `session.id`, then sort in ascending order. This helps you see the chronological flow ot traces within a session. 

